rder/BoundedOrder/Basic.html#OrderTop\">OrderTop</a> <span class=\"fn\">T</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">D</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">A</span> → <span class=\"fn\">T</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/MonoidAlgebra/Defs.html#AddMonoidAlgebra\">AddMonoidAlgebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Let `R` be a semiring, let `A` be an `AddZeroClass`, let `T` be an `OrderTop`,\nand let `D : A → T` be a \"degree\" function.\nFor an element `f : R[A]`, the element `infDegree f : T` is the infimum of all the elements in the\nsupport of `f`, or `⊤` if `f` is zero.\nOften, the Type `T` is `WithTop A`,\nIf, further, `A` has a linear order, then this notion coincides with the usual one,\nusing the minimum of the exponents. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/MonoidAlgebra/Degree.html#AddMonoidAlgebra.infDegree","kind":"def","line":586,"name":"AddMonoidAlgebra.infDegree","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Algebra/MonoidAlgebra/Degree.lean#L586-L594"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/MonoidAlgebra/Degree.html#AddMonoidAlgebra.Monic.supDegree_pow\"><span class=\"name\">AddMonoidAlgebra</span>.<span class=\"name\">Monic</span>.<span class=\"name\">supDegree_pow</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span clas