a</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/MonoidAlgebra/Degree.html#AddMonoidAlgebra.supDegree\">supDegree</a> <span class=\"fn\">D</span> (<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/MonoidAlgebra/Degree.html#AddMonoidAlgebra.supDegree\">supDegree</a> <span class=\"fn\">D</span> <span class=\"fn\">f</span></span> ⊔ <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/MonoidAlgebra/Degree.html#AddMonoidAlgebra.supDegree\">supDegree</a> <span class=\"fn\">D</span> <span class=\"fn\">g</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/MonoidAlgebra/Degree.html#AddMonoidAlgebra.supDegree_add_le","kind":"theorem","line":232,"name":"AddMonoidAlgebra.supDegree_add_le","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Algebra/MonoidAlgebra/Degree.lean#L232-L234"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/MonoidAlgebra/Degree.html#AddMonoidAlgebra.supDegree\"><span class=\"name\">AddMonoidAlgebra</span>.<span class=\"name\">supDegree</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">A</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">B</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_5}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#Semiring\">Semiring</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Lattice.html#SemilatticeSup\">SemilatticeSup</a> <span class=\"fn\">B</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/BoundedOrder/Basic.html#OrderBot\">OrderBot</a> <span class=\"fn\">B</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">D</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">A</span> → <span class=\"fn\">B</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/MonoidAlgebra/Defs.html#AddMonoidAlgebra\">AddMonoidAlgebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">B</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Let `R` be a semiring, let `A` be an `AddZeroClass`, let `B` be an `OrderBot`,\nand let `D : A → B` be a \"degree\" function.\nFor an element `f : R[A]`, the element `supDegree f : B` is the supremum of all the elements in the\nsupport of `f`, or `⊥` if `f` is zero.\nOften, the Type `B` is `WithBot A`,\nIf, further, `A` has a linear order, then this notion coincides with the usual one,\nusing the maximum of the exponents.\n\nIf `A := σ →₀ ℕ` then `R[A] = MvPolynomial σ R`, and if we equip `σ` with a linear order then\nthe induced linear order on `Lex A` equips `MvPolynomial` ring with a\n[monomial order](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monomial_order) (i.e. a linear order on `A`, the\ntype of (monic) monomials in `R[A]`, that respects addition). We make use of this monomial order\nby taking `D := toLex`, and different monomial orders could be accessed via different type\nsynonyms once they are added. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/MonoidAlgebra/Degree.html#AddMonoidAlgebra.supDegree","kind":"def","line":213,"name":"AddMonoidAlgebra.supDegree","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Algebra/MonoidAlgebra/Degree.lean#L213-L228"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/MonoidAlgebra/Degree.html#AddMonoidAlgebra.le_inf_support_finset_prod\"><span class=\"name\">AddMonoidAlgebra</span>.<span class=\"name\">le_inf_support_finset_prod</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">A</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">T</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ι</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_6}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Lattice.html#SemilatticeInf\">SemilatticeInf</a> <span class=\"fn\">T</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/BoundedOrder/Basic.html#OrderTop\">OrderTop</a> <span class=\"fn\">T</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><